---
import ServicePageLayout from '../layouts/ServicePageLayout.astro';

const faqSchemaObject = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do I know if my furnace needs repair?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Signs include unusual noises, uneven heating, rising energy bills, frequent cycling, or yellow burner flames instead of blue."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you offer emergency heating repair?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — we provide 24/7 emergency heating repair. If your furnace stops working in cold weather, call (714) 853-5534."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you repair all furnace brands?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "We repair Carrier, Trane, Goodman, Lennox, Rheem, York, and most other major furnace brands."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<ServicePageLayout
  title="Heating Repair in Stanton, CA | Hilo Heating and Air"
  description="Fast, reliable heating repair for homes and businesses in Stanton, CA. Emergency furnace repair with same-day service from licensed technicians at HiLo Heating & Air."
  heroTitle="Heating Repair in Stanton, CA"
  heroSubtitle="Heat goes out on the one cold week we actually get in Southern California. Hilo Heating and Air handles emergency heating repair for homes and businesses across Stanton."
  faqSchema={faqSchemaObject}
>
  <section class="pt-4 sm:pt-8 pb-16 sm:pb-24 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-lg">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-brand-blue mt-0 mb-4">What to Expect When You Call for Heating Repair</h2>

      <p>Heat goes out on the one cold week we actually get in Southern California, and suddenly everyone's reminded how much they take a working furnace for granted. If that's where you're at right now — cold house, no idea what's wrong — Hilo Heating and Air handles <strong>emergency heating repair</strong> for homes and businesses across Stanton, and we don't make you wait three days for someone to show up.</p>

      <h2>When It Can't Wait Until Monday</h2>
      <p>Some heating problems are minor annoyances. Others mean your house is genuinely cold and getting colder. No heat at all. A burning smell when the furnace kicks on. Strange clicking or banging noises. The pilot light won't stay lit. That's <strong>emergency heating repair</strong> territory, not a "we'll get to it next week" situation. Our trucks carry the parts techs actually need for most jobs, so you're not stuck waiting around for a part to ship in while it's 45 degrees inside.</p>
      <p>For older folks, young kids, or anyone with health conditions, a cold house isn't just uncomfortable — it can actually be risky. That's why our <strong>emergency heating repair</strong> line gets answered by an actual person, not a voicemail that promises a callback sometime tomorrow.</p>

      <h2>Furnace Trouble Specifically</h2>
      <p>Furnaces are usually the culprit when heat disappears entirely, and they fail in a handful of predictable ways — ignition problems, a clogged filter restricting airflow, a faulty thermostat, or a cracked heat exchanger, which is the kind of thing you actually want caught fast for safety reasons. If you're searching for <strong>furnace repair Los Angeles</strong> homeowners trust, it usually comes down to who diagnoses the problem correctly the first time instead of guessing and replacing parts that weren't actually broken.</p>
      <p>Our approach to <strong>furnace repair Los Angeles</strong> customers call us for starts with an actual diagnosis — not a guess, not an upsell pitch. We check the ignition system, the heat exchanger, the blower motor, electrical connections, and the thermostat before recommending anything. If it's a forty-dollar fix, that's what we tell you. We're not going to talk you into a new furnace because it's a bigger sale.</p>

      <h2>What Happens When You Call</h2>
      <p>You call, we ask a few quick questions to understand what's going on, and we give you a real timeframe — not a vague "sometime today" that turns into tomorrow. Once a tech's on site, you'll get a clear explanation of what's wrong and what it costs before any work starts. No surprise line items on the final bill.</p>

      <h2>Why People Call Hilo Heating and Air</h2>
      <p>We've built our name in Stanton on actually showing up and being honest about what's broken and what it'll cost to fix. Licensed, insured, and we've seen most of what can go wrong with a furnace at this point. We'd rather fix it right the first time than have you calling us back in two weeks for the same problem.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</ServicePageLayout>
